{'text': "The `@SpringBootApplication` annotation is a convenient shortcut for using three other annotations: `@Configuration`, `@EnableAutoConfiguration`, and `@ComponentScan`. It is commonly used to bootstrap a Spring Boot application.\n\nBy using `@SpringBootApplication`, you don't need to explicitly annotate your main class with these three annotations. Instead, the `@SpringBootApplication` annotation includes them with their default attributes.\n\nHere's an example of using `@SpringBootApplication`:\n\n```java\npackage com.example.myproject;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n\n@SpringBootApplication // same as @Configuration @EnableAutoConfiguration @ComponentScan\npublic class Application {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(Application.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe `@SpringBootApplication` annotation can also be used to customize the attributes of `@EnableAutoConfiguration` and `@ComponentScan`."}